Key Match Events: Marco Jansen took figures of 2/20 and also took two catches.
Ottneil Baartman finished with figures of 4/11.
David Miller contributed over half of South Africa's score with 59, unbeaten.
Scott Edwards reverse-scooped six off Nortje.
Teja Nidamanuru edged into the deep and was caught by Heinrich Klaasen.
Pre-Game Insights: South Africa named an unchanged side from their opening encounter against Sri Lanka.
Netherlands named an unchanged side from their opening encounter against Nepal.
Post-Match Reflections: Both teams struggled early in their respective innings, with South Africa losing four wickets in the first five overs and Netherlands struggling to reach 104.
